                        <div class="para-text">
                            Tarun Bharat Sangh (TBS), based in Rajasthan, is lead by Dr. Rajendra Singh - who is loveably referred as the water man of India. The group follows a Gandhian philosophy of helping the poor to help themselves. TBS is best known for doing ecological research
                            and land development to provide clean and fresh water to people. Over the last three decades, Tarun Bharat Sangh has built 402 structures over an area of 500 sq km in an arid portion of Rajasthan to rejuvenate the river, increasing
